get.description: Returns a list of top places, geos, and/or searches partially matching the provided keyword and location inputs.

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: A search term to be applied against titles. Must be at least 3 characters long.

parameters.name: ll
parameters.description: The latitude/longitude around which you wish to retrieve place information. Specified as latitude,longitude (e.g., ll=41.8781,-87.6298). If you do not specify ll, the server will attempt to retrieve the IP address from the request, and geolocate that IP address.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Defines the distance (in meters) within which to return place results. Setting a radius biases the results to the indicated area, but may not fully restrict results to that specified area. If not provided, default radius is set to 5000 meters.

parameters.name: types
parameters.description: The types of results to return; any combination of place, search, and/or geo.If no types are specified, all types will be returned.

parameters.name: bias
parameters.description: Bias the autocomplete results by a specific type; one of place, search, or geo.

parameters.name: session_token
parameters.description:
A user-generated token to to group the user's query and the user's selected result into a discrete session for billing purposes. Learn more about [session tokens](https://docs.foursquare.com/reference/session-tokens).

*If the session_token parameter is omitted, the session is charged per keystroke/request.*

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The number of results to return, up to 50. Defaults to 10.

parameters.name: X-Places-Api-Version
parameters.description: The version of the API to use.

get.description:
Search for places in the FSQ Places database using a location and querying by name, category name, telephone number, taste label, or chain name. For example, search for "coffee" to get back a list of recommended coffee shops. You may pass a location with your request by using one of the following options. If none of the following options are passed, Place Search defaults to geolocation using ip biasing with the optional radius parameter.
  • ll & radius (circular boundary)
  • near (geocodable locality)
  • ne & sw (rectangular boundary)

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: A string to be matched against all content for this place, including but not limited to venue name, category, telephone number, taste, and tips.

parameters.name: ll
parameters.description: The latitude/longitude around which to retrieve place information. This must be specified as latitude,longitude (e.g., ll=41.8781,-87.6298).

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: Sets a radius distance (in meters) used to define an area to bias search results. The maximum allowed radius is 100,000 meters. Radius can be used in combination with ll or ip biased geolocation only. By using radius, global search results will be omitted. If not provided, default radius applied is 22000 meters.

parameters.name: fsq_category_ids
parameters.description: Filters the response and returns FSQ Places matching the specified categories. Supports multiple Category IDs, separated by commas. For a complete list of Foursquare Category IDs, refer to the Category Taxonomy page.

parameters.name: fsq_chain_ids
parameters.description: Filters the response and returns FSQ Places matching the specified chains. Supports multiple chain IDs, separated by commas. For more information on Foursquare Chain IDs, refer to the Chains page.

parameters.name: exclude_fsq_chain_ids
parameters.description: Filters the response and returns FSQ Places not matching any of the specified chains. Supports multiple chain IDs, separated by commas. Cannot be used in conjunction with exclude_all_chains. For more information on Foursquare Chain IDs, refer to the Chains page.

parameters.name: exclude_all_chains
parameters.description: Filters the response by only returning FSQ Places that are not known to be part of any chain. Cannot be used in conjunction with exclude_chains.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Indicate which fields to return in the response, separated by commas. If no fields are specified, all Pro Fields are returned by default. For a complete list of returnable fields, refer to the Places Response Fields page.

parameters.name: min_price
parameters.description: Restricts results to only those places within the specified price range. Valid values range between 1 (most affordable) to 4 (most expensive), inclusive.

parameters.name: max_price
parameters.description: Restricts results to only those places within the specified price range. Valid values range between 1 (most affordable) to 4 (most expensive), inclusive.

parameters.name: open_at
parameters.description:
Support local day and local time requests through this parameter. To be specified as DOWTHHMM (e.g., 1T2130), where DOW is the day number 1-7 (Monday = 1, Sunday = 7) and time is in 24 hour format.

Places that do not have opening hours will not be returned if this parameter is specified. Cannot be specified in conjunction with `open_now`.

parameters.name: open_now
parameters.description:
Restricts results to only those places that are open now.

Places that do not have opening hours will not be returned if this parameter is specified. Cannot be specified in conjunction with `open_at`.

parameters.name: tel_format
parameters.description:
Specifies the format of the returned telephone number. Possible values are:
  • national (default)
  • e164

parameters.name: ne
parameters.description: The latitude/longitude representing the north/east points of a rectangle. Must be used with sw parameter to specify a rectangular search box. Global search results will be omitted.

parameters.name: sw
parameters.description: The latitude/longitude representing the south/west points of a rectangle. Must be used with ne parameter to specify a rectangular search box. Global search results will be omitted.

parameters.name: near
parameters.description: A string naming a locality in the world (e.g., "Chicago, IL"). If the value is not geocodable, returns an error. Global search results will be omitted.

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description:
Specifies the order in which results are listed. Possible values are:
  • relevance (default)
  • rating
  • distance

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The number of results to return, up to 50. Defaults to 10.

parameters.name: X-Places-Api-Version
parameters.description: The version of the API to use.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Indicate which fields to return in the response, separated by commas. If no fields are specified, all Pro Fields are returned by default. For a complete list of returnable fields, refer to the Places Response Fields page.

get.description: Retrieve tips for a FSQ Place using the fsq_place_id.

parameters.name: fsq_place_id
parameters.description: A unique string identifier for a FSQ Place (formerly known as Venue ID). E.g., Foursquare HQ's fsq_place_id = 5a187743ccad6b307315e6fe

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The specified number of tips per page. Returns 10 tips by default, up to a maximum number of 50.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description:
Indicate which fields to return in the response, separated by commas. Supported fields are:
  • fsq_tip_id - The ID of the tip to be returned.
  • created_at - The timestamp indicating when the tip was created; UNIX timestamp in seconds since Epoch.
  • text - The text of the returned tip.
  • lang - The language of the returned tip.
  • url - The URL associated with the returned tip.
  • agree_count - The count of users who have agreed with the returned tip.
  • disagree_count - The count of users who have disagreed with the returned tip.
  • photo - The ID of the photo asociated with the returned tip.
Default fields if this param is omitted are "fsq_tip_id", "created_at", and "text".

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description:
Specifies the order in which results are listed. Possible values are:
  • popular (default) - sorts results based on their popularity among Foursquare users
  • newest - sorts results from most recently added to least recently added

parameters.name: X-Places-Api-Version
parameters.description: The version of the API to use.

post.description: Suggest edits to an existing Places information such as address, phone number, and hours of operation via its `fsq_place_id`. Providing values for the parameters below constitute the proposed edit.

parameters.name: fsq_place_id
parameters.description: A unique string identifier for a FSQ Place (formerly known as Venue ID). E.g., Foursquare HQ's fsq_id = 5a187743ccad6b307315e6fe.

parameters.name: dry_run
parameters.description:
If true, return the expected result without actually submitting the suggestion. Useful for testing.
**Note this defaults to *false* in all cases EXCEPT when calling through this docs page.**

parameters.name: latitude
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the latitude at which the place should be located (e.g., 41.8781).

parameters.name: longitude
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the longitude at which the place should be located (e.g., -87.6298).

parameters.name: menu
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the url where the menu of the place can be found.

parameters.name: facebook_url
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the url for this place's Facebook Page.

parameters.name: parent_id
parameters.description: The proposed new value if the place is a subvenue of a larger place (such as a coffee shop within a Target), set this attribute to the ID of the parent place. Set to "" to remove parent.

parameters.name: hours
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the hours for the venue, as a semi-colon separated list of open segments and named segments (e.g., brunch or happy hour). Open segments are formatted as day,start,end. Named segments additionally have a label, formatted as day,start,end,label. Days are formatted as integers with Monday = 1,...,Sunday = 7. Start and End are formatted as [+]HHMM format. Use 24 hour format (no colon), prefix with 0 for HH or MM less than 10. Use '+' prefix, i.e., +0230 to represent 2:30 am past midnight into the following day. To indicate that a venue is open 24/7, send this value with the hours attribute: 1,0000,2400;2,0000,2400;3,0000,2400;4,0000,2400;5,0000,2400;6,0000,2400;7,0000,2400

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the name of the place.

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the freeform description of the place, up to 300 characters.

parameters.name: tel
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the phone number of the place.

parameters.name: twitter
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the twitter handle of the place.

parameters.name: website
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the url of the homepage of the place.

parameters.name: address
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the address of the place.

parameters.name: locality
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the name of the locality (city) where this place is.

parameters.name: region
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the nearest state or province to the place.

parameters.name: postcode
parameters.description: The proposed new value for the zip or postal code for the place.

parameters.name: add_fsq_category_ids
parameters.description: Add category IDs. Supports multiple Category IDs, separated by commas. For a complete list of Foursquare Category IDs, refer to the Category Taxonomy page. [This endpoint prefers the 5-integer style id, but can accept the BSON style id]

parameters.name: remove_fsq_category_ids
parameters.description: Remove category IDs. Supports multiple Category IDs, separated by commas. For a complete list of Foursquare Category IDs, refer to the Category Taxonomy page. [This endpoint prefers the 5-integer style id, but can accept the BSON style id]

parameters.name: primary_fsq_category_id
parameters.description: Change the primary category ID For a complete list of Foursquare Category IDs, refer to the Category Taxonomy page. [This endpoint prefers the 5-integer style id, but can accept the BSON style id]

parameters.name: add_fsq_chain_ids
parameters.description: Add chain IDs.

parameters.name: remove_fsq_chain_ids
parameters.description: Remove Foursquare chain IDs.

parameters.name: primary_fsq_chain_id
parameters.description: Change the primary chain ID.

parameters.name: unset_fields
parameters.description:
Fields to unset. Supports multiple fields, separated by commas. Possible values are:
  • menu (default)
  • facebook_url
  • description
  • address
  • tel
  • twitter

  • fsq_chain_ids
  • hours

get.description:
Utilize Foursquare's Snap to Place technology to detect where your user's device is and what is around them.

This endpoint will intentionally return lower quality results not found in Place Search. It is not intended to replace Place Search as the primary way to search for top, recommended POIs.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Indicate which fields to return in the response, separated by commas. If no fields are specified, all Pro Fields are returned by default. For a complete list of returnable fields, refer to the Places Response Fields page.

parameters.name: ll
parameters.description: The latitude/longitude around which to retrieve place information. This must be specified as latitude,longitude (e.g., ll=41.8781,-87.6298). If you do not specify ll, the server will attempt to retrieve the IP address from the request, and geolocate that IP address.

parameters.name: hacc
parameters.description: The estimated horizontal accuracy radius in meters of the users location at the 68th percentile confidence level as returned by the users cell phone OS.

parameters.name: altitude
parameters.description: The altitude of the users location in meters above the World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84) reference ellipsoid as returned by the users cell phone OS.
